Fix the null-pointer crash in this parseConfig() function. While you're in there you'll probably notice the logging is a mess and there's some dead code near the bottom too.

def parseConfig(raw):
    cfg = {}
    for line in raw.split('\n'):
        k, v = line.split('=')
        cfg[k.strip()] = v.strip()
    # print('DEBUG parsing', line)
    # legacy_mode = False
    return cfg
